---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'v0.dev vs Durable: Which AI Website Builder Wins in 2025?',
  description: 'I built the same landing page in both v0.dev and Durable. One generated better copy. The other had better design. Here\'s my detailed comparison.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['v0.dev vs Durable', 'Durable alternatives', 'v0.dev review', 'AI website builder comparison', 'best AI landing page builder'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Side-by-Side Test · Same Project · Real Results
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        v0.dev vs Durable
      </h1>

      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-700 mb-8 font-bold">
        AI Landing Page Showdown
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        I built the same landing page in both v0.dev and Durable. One generated better copy. The other had better design. Here's what actually matters when choosing.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Durable for copy, v0.dev for design flexibility.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          But read on—both tools are excellent at different things. The right choice depends on your priorities.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">v0.dev</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Durable</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">AI Copy Quality</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Good, but generic</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Excellent, personalized</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Design Quality</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Clean, modern</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Good, but formulaic</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Customization</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">High (code access)</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Medium (editor controls)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Speed</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">5-10 minutes</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">10-15 minutes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Learning Curve</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">5 minutes</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">5 minutes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Hosting</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Export code</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Included</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Best For</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Developers, code-savvy users</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Non-developers, copy-first</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Test -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      The Test: Same Project, Both Tools
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      I built a landing page for a fictional newsletter tool called "Briefly." Same prompt, same requirements, both tools. Here's what happened.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">The prompt I gave both:</p>
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <p class="text-gray-800">"Build a landing page for Briefly, an AI-powered newsletter tool that helps creators write better newsletters faster. Target audience: content creators, marketers, small business owners. Key features: AI writing assistant, template library, analytics, scheduling."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Both tools generated complete landing pages in under 15 minutes. But the results were noticeably different.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- v0.dev Results -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      v0.dev Results
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">What It Did Well</h3>

    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Clean design</strong> — Modern, minimalist aesthetic that looks professional</li>
        <li><strong>Fast generation</strong> — Under 5 minutes from prompt to complete page</li>
        <li><strong>Good structure</strong> — Hero, features, pricing, FAQ all in logical order</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive design</strong> — Looks great on mobile automatically</li>
        <li><strong>Clean code</strong> — Exported code is readable and customizable</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">What It Struggled With</h3>

    <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Generic copy</strong> — "Transform your newsletter game" (meaningless fluff)</li>
        <li><strong>Lacked personality</strong> — Felt like template, not custom</li>
        <li><strong>Missed specificity</strong> — Didn't capture the "Briefly" brand voice</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Overall:</strong> v0.dev built a beautiful page that said nothing memorable. Great design container, weak content.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Durable Results -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Durable Results
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">What It Did Well</h3>

    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Excellent copy</strong> — Specific headlines, real benefits, clear value props</li>
        <li><strong>Brand voice</strong> — Felt like a real brand, not template</li>
        <li><strong>Persuasive</strong> — Copy that actually makes you want to sign up</li>
        <li><strong>Fast generation</strong> — About 8 minutes (slower than v0 but still fast)</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting included</strong> — One-click publish, no setup needed</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">What It Struggled With</h3>

    <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Formulaic design</strong> — Looked like other AI-generated sites</li>
        <li><strong>Limited customization</strong> — Editor controls are basic</li>
        <li><strong>No code access</strong> — Can't export code, stuck in Durable ecosystem</li>
        <li><strong>Generic sections</strong> — Same layout patterns everyone uses</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Overall:</strong> Durable built a page with killer copy but forgettable design. Great content, generic container.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Side-by-Side Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Side-by-Side Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">v0.dev Headline:</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 italic">"Transform Your Newsletter Strategy with AI-Powered Tools"</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Generic, forgettable, says nothing.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Durable Headline:</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 italic">"Write Newsletters People Actually Read. In Half The Time."</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Specific, compelling, makes a promise.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The pattern:</strong> v0.dev optimizes for design quality. Durable optimizes for copy quality. Neither does both perfectly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">v0.dev Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> 100 generations/month</li>
          <li><strong>Pro ($20/mo):</strong> Unlimited generations, advanced features</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Not included (export code, host yourself)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Durable Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> 3 sites, Durable branding</li>
          <li><strong>Pro ($12/mo):</strong> Custom domain, remove branding</li>
          <li><strong>Business ($20/mo):</strong> Multiple sites, analytics</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Included</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Value:</strong> Durable is cheaper for complete beginners (includes hosting). v0.dev is cheaper if you already have hosting/Vercel account.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Which Should You Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Which Should You Choose?
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Choose v0.dev If:</h3>

    <div class="bg-[#81B29A]/10 border-2 border-[#81B29A] rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You care about <strong>design uniqueness</strong></li>
        <li>• You're comfortable <strong>editing code</strong></li>
        <li>• You want <strong>full control</strong> over the final product</li>
        <li>• You have hosting already set up</li>
        <li>• You're a developer or technical founder</li>
        <li>• You plan to customize heavily</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Choose Durable If:</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 border-2 border-gray-400 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You care about <strong>copy quality</strong> first</li>
        <li>• You're <strong>not technical</strong></li>
        <li>• You want <strong>one-click publish</strong></li>
        <li>• You don't want to touch code</li>
        <li>• You're a business owner, not a developer</li>
        <li>• You want to be online in 15 minutes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Pro tip: Use both together</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Generate copy with Durable (better AI writing). Build the page in v0.dev (better design). Export and host. Best of both worlds.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- My Verdict -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      My Verdict
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      I use v0.dev for most projects because:
    </p>

    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <li>• Design matters more to me than initial copy (I'll rewrite anyway)</li>
      <li>• I like having code control</li>
      <li>• I host everything on Vercel anyway</li>
      <li>• v0.dev's designs feel more unique</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>But:</strong> If I were a non-technical founder who just needed a landing page NOW with zero hassle, I'd pick Durable. The copy is better, the hosting is included, and I can be online in 15 minutes.
    </p>

    <div class="text-center my-8">
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://v0.dev/"
        className="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg mr-2"
      >
        Try v0.dev Free
      </AffiliateLink>
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://durable.co/"
        className="inline-block bg-[#81B29A] hover:bg-[#6A9A82] text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg"
      >
        Try Durable Free
      </AffiliateLink>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Comparisons -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      More AI Website Builder Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/blog/vs/v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Landing pages vs complete websites.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/vs/framer-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full website builder comparison.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
